\left|\int_{C_R}\frac{dz}{1+z^n}\right|\leq \left(\frac{2\pi R}{n}\right)\left(\frac{1}{R^{n}-1}\right)\rightarrow0\;\;\;as\;\;R\rightarrow\infty.
\int_{[R,Re^{2\pi i/n}]}\frac{dz}{1+z^n}=\int_{R}^{0}\frac{e^{2\pi i/n}dr}{1+r^n}.
\lim_{R\rightarrow\infty}\int_{\gamma_R}\frac{dz}{1+z^n}=\lim_{R\rightarrow\infty}\int_{[0,R]}\frac{dx}{1+x^n}+\int_{[R,Re^{2\pi i/n}]}\frac{dx}{1+x^n}+\int_{C_R}\frac{dx}{1+x^n}=(1-e^{2\pi i/n})I_n\;\;\;(1).
